				{
					"@type": "TVEpisode",
					"episodeNumber": "2.7",
					"name": "Where Pleasant Fountains Lie",
					"datePublished": "2021-09-23",
					"workTranslation": {
						"@type": "TVEpisode",
						"inLanguage": "de",
						"name": "Wo die lust’gen Quellen liegen",
						"datePublished": "2021-09-24"
					},
					"director": {
						"@id": "https://bittersmann.de/startrek/people#JasonZurek",
						"@type": "Person",
						"name": "Jason Zurek"
					},
					"description": {
						"en": "Queen Paolana, ruler of Hysperia—a Renaissance-styled society from a planet colonized by fantasy enthusiasts—hails the Cerritos to ask for help from her son, Lieutenant Commander Andarithio Billups. Billups reluctantly agrees to look at her ship’s engines, wary of his mother’s repeated attempts to lure him back to their kingdom by having him lose his virginity, which, by Hysperian tradition, would result in him ascending to the throne as king. Boimler is disappointed after he is reassigned from an exciting field mission to escorting a malevolent AI named AGIMUS with Mariner. Their ship crash lands on a desert planet, where AGIMUS attempts to sow discord by revealing that Mariner had Boimler reassigned as she did not believe he was capable of the field mission. Boimler tricks AGIMUS into powering a distress signal, impressing Mariner who apologizes for getting Boimler reassigned. When Billups believes that Paolana is killed in an explosion, he prepares to lose his virginity and ascend to the throne, but this was a ruse and Rutherford stops Billups in time.",
						"de": "Die USS Cerritos hilft dem Schiff von Königin Paolana, der Herrscherin von Hysperia und Mutter von Billups. Diese will, dass ihr Sohn endlich Sex hat, damit er seinen Platz in der Thronfolge einnehmen kann. Sie inszeniert eine Explosion, bei der sie und Rutherford scheinbar getötet werden. Tendi ist von Rutherfords Tod erschüttert, bemerkt jedoch, dass er und Paolana am Leben sind. Sie verhindert gerade noch rechtzeitig, dass Billups seine Jungfräulichkeit verliert. Mariner und Boimler sollen den manipulativen Agimus-Computer zum Daystrom-Institut transportieren und stürzen mit dem Shuttle auf einem Wüstenplaneten ab. Obwohl Agimus seine Hilfe anbietet, vertrauen die beiden ihm nicht. Als er die beiden gegeneinander aufzuhetzen versucht, überlistet ihn Boimler, nutzt seine Batterie aus und sendet eine Notsignal. Der Computer endet im Gefängnis böser Rechenmaschinen."
					},
