				{
					"@type": "TVEpisode",
					"episodeNumber": "3.10",
					"name": "The Stars At Night",
					"datePublished": "2022-10-27",
					"workTranslation": {
						"@type": "TVEpisode",
						"inLanguage": "de",
						"name": "Die Sterne in der Nacht",
						"datePublished": "2022-10-28"
					},
					"director": {
						"@id": "https://bittersmann.de/startrek/people#JasonZurek",
						"@type": "Person",
						"name": "Jason Zurek"
					},
					"description": {
						"en": "In the wake of Victoria Nuzé’s embarrassing expose, Starfleet opts to follow Admiral Buenamigo’s proposal to decommission all California-class ships and replace Second Contact duties with his automated Texas-class ships. Captain Freeman challenges Buenamigo’s ships to a race to run their duties. Rutherford is intrigued by the new ships’ programming. Meanwhile, Mariner becomes suspicious of her and Petra’s mysterious benefactor, but learns that it’s funded by Jean-Luc Picard. She confesses to Petra that she may have been searching for a reason to return to Starfleet. During the race, the Cerritos barely keeps up with the Texas-class ship’s capabilities and loses when the crew must pause their work to rescan for life on a desolate planet. Freeman realizes that the Texas-class having failed to stop and scan for life proves that the ships are inadequate to handle Second Contact parameters. She informs Buenamigo about reporting this information to Starfleet when Rutherford bursts in. He recognizes the Texas-class’s A.I. programming as his own and has realized that the shadowy Starfleet official who erased his memory was Buenamigo. Buenamigo reveals that he set up the Cerritos all along hoping they would fail in favor of the Texas-class. Rutherford warns him not to bring the ships to full automation, as the A.I. code is the same as Badgey’s and could result in aggressiveness. Buenamigo ignores him and brings the ships online, ordering them to destroy the Cerritos to cover his tracks, but they attack the starbase, killing him, before attacking the Cerritos. Hopelessly outmatched, Freeman sends out a distress signal, which is answered by Mariner and Petra, who also summon all the other California-class ships to assist. The Texas-class ships are defeated. Later, the crews of the California-class ships celebrate, and Freeman apologizes to Mariner, who forgives her and rejoins the Cerritos. T’lyn arrives as the Science Department’s newest recruit under Tendi’s mentorship. Meanwhile, Rutherford’s original implant, containing Badgey’s corrupted A.I., are collected from the Kalla system by an unknown source.",
						"de": "Sternzeit 58499,2: Admiral Buenamigo überzeugt die Sterenenflottenführung, die Cerritos und alle anderen Schiffe der California-Klasse zu verschrotten und durch vollautomatische Schiffe der Texas-Klasse zu ersetzen. Captain Freeman will das verhindern und vereinbart ein Wettrennen zwischen der Cerritos und einem vollautomatischen Texas-Schiff. Die Cerritos verliert, weil sie auf LT-358 Indizien für unbekannte Lebensformen pflichtgemäß überprüft. Es stellt sich jedoch heraus, dass Rutherford an der Programmierung der Texas-Klasse beteiligt war, bevor Buenamigo sein Gedächtnis löschen ließ und Rutherford auf die Cerritos kam. Damit dies nicht bekannt wird, befiehlt Buenamigo seinen Schiffen, die Cerritos zu zerstören. Rutherford erkennt, dass seine Programmierung genauso fehlerhaft war wie die von Badgey (siehe Episode 6). Deshalb wenden sich die Texas-Schiffe gegen Buenamigo, bevor sie die Cerritos angreifen. Mariner, die sich nach der Cerritos zurückgesehnt hat, ruft alle Schiffe der California-Klasse zusammen und vereint können sie die Texas-Schiffe zerstören."
					},
